  "texts": [
    "The dataset was gathered in January 2019 over 32 traversals of a central Oxford route and includes a variety of weather, traffic, and lighting conditions.",
    "In addition to the raw sensor recordings from all sensors, this dataset provides an updated set of calibrations, ground truth trajectories for the radar sensor as well as MATLAB and Python development tools for leveraging the data.",
    "MulRan (Kim et al. 2020): MulRan is a multimodal range dataset for radar and LiDAR specifically targeting the urban environment.",
    "It focuses on the 3D-PCPR problem and provides 6D baseline trajectories of a vehicle for place recognition ground truth.",
    "MulRan captures both temporal and structural diversities for 3D place recognition research."
  ],
